      • readItem

        @NotNull
@NotNull List<@NotNull Object> readItem​(@Nullable
                                        @Nullable Object parentInstance,
                                        boolean requiresJsonKey,
                                        @NotNull
                                        @NotNull IJsonParsingContext context)
                                 throws IOException
        Reads a JSON/YAML object storing the associated data in the Java object parentInstance.

        When called the current JsonToken of the JsonParser is expected to be a JsonToken.START_OBJECT.

        After returning the current JsonToken of the JsonParser is expected to be the next token after the JsonToken.END_OBJECT for this class.

        Parameters:
        parentInstance - the parent Java object to store the data in
        requiresJsonKey - when true indicates that the item will have a JSON key
        context - the parsing context
        Returns:
        the instances or an empty list if no data was parsed
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurred while reading the parsed content

      • readItem

        @NotNull
@NotNull Object readItem​(@Nullable
                         @Nullable Object parentInstance,
                         @NotNull
                         @NotNull StartElement start,
                         @NotNull
                         @NotNull IXmlParsingContext context)
                  throws IOException,
                         XMLStreamException
        Reads a XML element storing the associated data in a Java class instance, returning the resulting instance.

        When called the next XMLEvent of the XMLStreamReader2 is expected to be a XMLStreamConstants.START_ELEMENT that is the XML element associated with the Java class.

        After returning the next XMLEvent of the XMLStreamReader2 is expected to be a the next event after the XMLStreamConstants.END_ELEMENT for the XML XMLStreamConstants.START_ELEMENT element associated with the Java class.

        Parameters:
        parentInstance - the Java instance for the object containing this object
        start - the containing start element
        context - the parsing context
        Returns:
        the instance or null if no data was parsed
        Throws:
        IOException - if an error occurred while reading the parsed content
        XMLStreamException - if an error occurred while parsing the content as XML
